00:00:54.610 --> 00:00:56.450
First up, the man
who's now credited

00:00:56.450 --> 00:00:58.180
with starting it
all, James Mason,

00:00:58.180 --> 00:01:00.514
better known as Skookum Jim.

00:01:00.514 --> 00:01:02.930
Skookum was a Canadian native
who originally packed mining

00:01:02.930 --> 00:01:05.590
supplies up the
snowy Chilkoot pass.

00:01:05.590 --> 00:01:07.900
Now, this pass was
serious, you guys.

00:01:07.900 --> 00:01:10.320
Seven miles through
icy, glacial rocks

00:01:10.320 --> 00:01:13.120
that climbed up over 3,000 feet.

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:15.540
Legend has it that
he single-handedly

00:01:15.540 --> 00:01:19.150
156 pounds of bacon up the pass.

00:01:19.150 --> 00:01:21.687
When he first discovered
the gold at Rabbit Creek,

